summaries.short: As the Wiccan-vampire standoff reaches a critical juncture, Sookie summons her faerie powers to stop Marnie's evil plan.
summaries.full: As the Wiccan-vampire standoff reaches a critical juncture, Sookie summons her faerie powers to prevent Marnie from bewitching Bill, Eric and Pam into a suicide march, while Jesus casts a secret spell designed to un-bind Antonia and break the witch's deadly defenses. Sam settles a score with Marcus; Andy finds unexpected passion in the forest; Lafayette is consumed by the past.

summaries.short: Season Four Finale. Spirits of the dead converge on Bon Temps as Sookie and her two favorite vampires battle Marnie's latest incarnation.
summaries.full: Season Four Finale. It's Samhain, Wicca's greatest holy day, and spirits of the dead surface in Bon Temps, giving Sookie some valuable allies to combat Marnie's newest incarnation. As Season Four comes to a shattering conclusion, Debbie confronts Sookie and Tara with deadly consequences, and the denizens of Bon Temps brace for a new crisis with a familiar face.

summaries.short: As all hell breaks loose in Shreveport, Sookie summons her most potent powers yet to save Bill.
summaries.full: As all hell breaks loose in Shreveport, Sookie summons her most potent powers yet to save Bill, in the process breaking a spell and leading Marnie/Antonia to re-evaluate her mission. Later, Jesus, Sookie, Lafayette and Jason try to breach the Moongoddess Emporium's defenses to liberate Tara and Holly, while Bill leads a brigade of vampires committed to destroying the place.

summaries.short: Season Five Premiere. Sookie and Lafayette clean up the Tara and Debbie Pelt mess; Bill and Eric are visited by the Vampire Authority.
summaries.full: Season 5 Premiere. Sookie and Lafayette struggle with what to do about Tara; Bill and Eric are visited by the Vampire Authority; Alcide's werewolf pack comes after Sam; Jessica enjoys her new freedom; Jason is visited by the recently turned Reverend Steve Newlin; Terry's PTSD is reignited; Alcide warns Sookie about the recently resurfaced Russell Edgington.

Jesus tries to purge the restless spirit out of Lafayette; Marcus enlists Alcide to help him deal with the Sam situation. Despite Tara and Holly's misgivings, Marnie plots her next move against the vampires, during a 'Festival of Tolerance' event at Shreveport.

summaries.full: Tara resurfaces in Bon Temps. Bill and Eric meet Salome. Pam recalls her human life, and her first encounter with Eric. Werewolves J.D. and Rikki pay tribute to Marcus, but Alcide refuses to participate or to take his rightful place as the new packmaster. Fearing Russell's return, Sookie procures a home-protection system; Arlene looks into Terry's erratic behavior.
